<h3 class="western">Recommended Textbooks</h3>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0.51cm">There is no textbook required. The
following books and documents are recommended for reading in addition
to my lectures: 
</p>
<ul>
	<li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.51cm">R. Gray (2001), <a href="slides%20and%20notes/graybook.pdf">Advanced
	Statistical Computing</a> (PDF), online lecture notes. 
	</p>
	<li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.51cm">G.L. Jones (2007),
	<a href="slides%20and%20notes/GalinJonesNotes.pdf">Computational
	Statistical Methods</a> (PDF), online lecture notes.</p>
	<li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.51cm">John H. Mathews, <a href="http://mathfaculty.fullerton.edu/mathews/numerical.html" target="_blank">A
	Website Containing Animations for Illustrating Numerical Methods</a>.</p>
	<li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.51cm">Some of my own lectures,
	available from the folder “<b>slides and notes</b>” in the
	course website.</p>
</ul>
